Co-Author Post


21 Sep 2019 17:05






Floppy was a joy to work with! She was very patient and our ideas worked very well together. ^^

So I was searching through the wikimedia commons a few months back and found this picture. I showed it to the team bird members, and not_a_seagull helped me brainstorm for it. Months passed, and I never did anything with it.

I asked Floppy recently if she wanted to collab, and she said yes! A few weeks later we began brainstorming, and I brought up the idea Seagull had helped me with. Floppy suggested some changes that we both liked, and we got to work!

This piece means a lot to me because I wrote a lot of the dialogue, the first two interviews (floppy tweaked the second one by adding some things that only made it better!) and I helped characterize Goshawk and created Nour, which were important later on. Anyone who knows me, knows I’m abysmal with dialogue. But the fact that I was able to write good dialogue on pretty much first try means a lot to me. And, I love what Flopoy did with Nour and Goshawk later on!

Idk I ramble, but thanks to Floppy so much for working with me!

And of course, thanks to those who crit this. ^^







